<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="609" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">
2.1-2.3 mm, 2.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide (
<bibRefCitation author="Bright, DE" journalOrPublisher="Koleopterologische Rundschau" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="389 - 428" refId="B14" refString="Bright, DE, Torres, JA, 2006. Studies on the West Indian Scolytidae (Coleoptera) 4. A review of the Scolytidae of Puerto Rico, U. S. A. with descriptions of one new genus, fourteen new species and notes on new synonymy (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau 76: 389 - 428" title="Studies on the West Indian Scolytidae (Coleoptera) 4. A review of the Scolytidae of Puerto Rico, U. S. A. with descriptions of one new genus, fourteen new species and notes on new synonymy (Coleoptera: Scolytidae)." volume="76" year="2006">Bright and Torres 2006</bibRefCitation>
). This species is distinguished by the elytral apex feebly acuminate, declivital interstriae unarmed along its entire length, and antennal club with three sutures on posterior face.
</paragraph>
